<h2>United States Voice Assistant Users</h2>
<p>The United States remains the largest single voice market in dollar terms. User counts have grown every year for the past decade, and the platform mix has consolidated around three providers.</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>The number of voice search users in the United States is projected to reach <strong>157.1 million by end of 2026</strong>. (<a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/1384575/voice-assistant-users-united-states/">Statista</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The United States voice assistant user base hit <strong>153.5 million in 2025</strong>, a 2.5% year-over-year increase. (<a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/1384575/voice-assistant-users-united-states/">Statista</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>149.8 million United States voice users</strong> were recorded in 2024. (<a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/1384575/voice-assistant-users-united-states/">Statista</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Google Assistant leads</strong> the United States market with <strong>91.9 million users</strong>, followed by Siri at 86.5 million and Alexa at 77.2 million. (<a href="https://www.emarketer.com/content/us-voice-assistant-user-forecast">eMarketer</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>50% of United States consumers</strong> report using voice search every day. (<a href="https://www.synup.com/en/voice-search-statistics">Synup</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Among adults aged 25 to 34, the daily United States voice search rate climbs to <strong>58%</strong>. (<a href="https://www.synup.com/en/voice-search-statistics">Synup</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>58.6% of United States consumers</strong> have tried voice search at least once. (<a href="https://keywordseverywhere.com/blog/voice-search-statistics/">Keywords Everywhere</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>41% of United States adults</strong> use voice search on a daily basis. (<a href="https://bloggingwizard.com/voice-search-statistics/">Blogging Wizard</a>)</p>
</li>
</ol>
<h2>Smart Speaker Adoption Statistics</h2>
<p>Smart speakers represent the most visible voice hardware category, but the broader voice ecosystem now extends far beyond dedicated devices. The data shows where dedicated speakers stand and where the channel is moving.</p>
