</li>
<li>
<p>The <strong>global smart speaker market</strong> is projected to reach <strong>23.32 billion dollars in 2026</strong>. (<a href="https://www.imarcgroup.com/smart-speaker-market">IMARC Group</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Smart speaker market revenue is forecast to surge to <strong>52.44 billion dollars by 2030</strong> at a 22.5% compound annual growth rate. (<a href="https://www.imarcgroup.com/smart-speaker-market">IMARC Group</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>52% of smart speaker users</strong> report using their devices every single day. (<a href="https://www.edisonresearch.com/the-infinite-dial-2025/">Edison Research</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>52% of smart speakers</strong> sit in the family room, <strong>25% in bedrooms</strong>, and <strong>22% in kitchens</strong>. (<a href="https://www.edisonresearch.com/the-infinite-dial-2025/">Edison Research</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
