</li>
</ol>
<h2>Voice Search Accuracy Statistics</h2>
<p>Voice assistant accuracy has improved dramatically over the past five years. The current generation of large language models drives a meaningful step change in answer quality, though gaps between assistants remain.</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Across all major voice assistants, queries are answered correctly <strong>93.7% of the time</strong> on average. (<a href="https://www.demandsage.com/voice-search-statistics/">DemandSage</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Google Assistant understands 100% of voice queries</strong> and answers them correctly <strong>92.9% of the time</strong>. (<a href="https://www.demandsage.com/voice-search-statistics/">DemandSage</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Siri understands 99.8% of queries</strong> and provides a correct answer <strong>83.1% of the time</strong>. (<a href="https://www.demandsage.com/voice-search-statistics/">DemandSage</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Alexa understands 99.9% of queries</strong> but answers correctly only <strong>79.8% of the time</strong>, the lowest of the three. (<a href="https://www.demandsage.com/voice-search-statistics/">DemandSage</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The average Word Error Rate (WER) for modern voice systems sits at <strong>3.5% for clean speech</strong>, climbing to <strong>12% in noisy environments</strong> and <strong>15% for strong regional accents</strong>. (<a href="https://voicetonotes.com/voice-recognition-accuracy/">VoiceToNotes Research</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>On-device voice processing grew from 12% to 38%</strong> of queries between 2022 and 2025 as Apple, Google, and Amazon shifted to local AI models. (<a href="https://www.demandsage.com/voice-search-statistics/">DemandSage</a>)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>47% of voice users</strong> say on-device processing would directly increase their trust in voice assistants. (<a href="https://www.demandsage.com/voice-search-statistics/">DemandSage</a>)</p>
</li>
</ol>
